	   <tr><td colspan=2>I started a new Shaman too, an Ogre.&nbsp;&nbsp;I pumped up his WIS as much as I could and left the rest to go to my STA.  <br><br>Like he said, STA=HP=Mana for a Shaman, so don't forget that.  Also, in the first 30 levels of the game, there's a good chance you'll be meleeing, so the extra HP will be very useful.<br><br>I like the Ogre Shaman because of the innate skills and stats, such as 130 base STR, unstunnable from the front, and the SLAM ability.  Sure, KOS races are a pain to play sometimes, and ogres get a small XP penalty, but it's crazy fun to play, like a tank with magic.<br>&nbsp;<br>-----------------------<br>Rogues do it from behind.<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105276</a> <br>Tyrlinoth Arkonnen - The Nameless</td></tr>
