<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103584041139105></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103584041139105><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=103584041139105>RE: Newbie!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=103584041139105#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2440><span id=Scholar>Dargadin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>370 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 28th 4:46 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.76]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I do recall being rather cross that all the armor quests seemed to begin at lvl 20 or so.&nbsp;&nbsp;When I was your level, I took up sewing as a way to get some better armor, and later blacksmithing to make myself banded armor.<br><br>Around 20-25 you can start doing the Totemic armor quests.  While totemic pieces have good AC, they don't have WIS bonuses except for the helmet.  Though the quests are tough, and you'd be surprised how inexpensive totemic armor is to buy.<br><br>What I wore for most of my career was Imbued Northman Ringmail.  Each piece gives +2 WIS, +1 STR, and +2 SvCold, and a better AC than banded. <br><br>At this point, if you can afford 100pp, is to buy a full suit of banded armor.<br><br>Hope this helps!<br>&nbsp;<br>______________________________________<br><b>Dargadin, Barbarian Shaman of the 53rd Season</b><br>Darg&nbsp;&nbsp; 41 Barb Warrior<br>Cyrius 21 Eru Wizard<br><b><span style='color: blue;'>Legions of Ragnorak</span style='color: blue;'><br>Ayonae Ro Server</b></td></tr>
