<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=103312578198319></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103312578198319><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=103312578198319>Leveling guide</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=103312578198319#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145598><span id= >DarkdirkCauldronborne</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>45 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 27th 7:39 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.06]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I lvled from 1-24 in very little time, sometimes lvling 4-5 times per day.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here is what I did, if anyone finds this useful.<br><br>Now to do this, you may need to get a few buffs.  I also was a little twinked, but nevertheless this is a good guide.  You will do all your fighting in luclin.<br><br>Here is the basic guide: 1-5 shar vahl, 6-8 shadeweavers, 9-24 paludal caverns<br><br>Start off by going to nexus at lvl 1, getting a bind in SH, then running to shar vahl.  To do this, run through Paludal caverns (definitely get invis) and then running through shadeweavers or hollowshade to shar vahl.  Try to get some buffs in the bazaar while you are there.<br><br>Once in shar vahl, get a bind.  Then level from 1-5 fighting in the crater beneath the city (accessable by walking down the ledge near the bridge to either of the zones.) This place is safe, very few creatures are kos, and they are rare.  Nothing is social, and guards are nearby.<br><br>Once you are level 5, head to shadeweavers.  Fight hoppers, the large beetles, and shades.  As you level move up to hunters, saureks, and loda'kai poachers.  There is a poacher camp out from shar vahl.  Don't try the camp alone, but you can snag the poachers that wander out. I suggest pulling to the road to avoid adds.<br><br>Once you are lvl 8 or 9, head to paludal caverns.  This place is the best exp you will ever get in Everquest.  Dungeon bonus and luclin exp bonus.  Start out by killing the mud burrowers by the shadeweavers zone in the tunnel and around the lake.  Careful, they are social but are very weak for their level.  You can also kill sensate reishi sprouts, they are not social.  As you level up, start killing muck diggers around the lake.  They are social with mud burrowers.<br><br>Around level 11 or 12, hug the wall and head left from the shadeweavers zone until you reach a small tunnel by the lake.  Go in, head right then left.  I believe this takes you to a tunnel with higher lvl shrooms and grime tunnelers.  I hunted these from 11-14 (you could stay til 16), but I am betting they are too high for most.  If you can't handle the monsters in this tunnel, continue to hunt muck diggers.<br><br>You can also head backwards and to the right, which will lead you to a small lake with phlerg phlarg fiends.  They hit kinda hard, and proc a nasty low dot that CAN kill you if you don't pay attention for a long time.  It's called Spreading Crud, and its worse than Rabies.  Instead of waiting the hours needed for it to go away, cast cure disease 3 times.  Voila, its gone.<br><br>After this, head back to shadow haven.  I couldn't get invis, so I sowed myself and ran for it.  Don't try unless you know the area well, because I had 15 fiends behind me in the end.  Bind in SH, and start hunting the higher lvl patog phlarg fiends up on the ledge past the recondite camp to the right if you are facing away from shadow haven.  Be careful, a few wander.  Once you are lvl 17 or 18, try to get a group for recondites.  They are the bandits that have two camps.  One in front of SH, and one around the lake to the left.  They one near SH is called b1, the other b2.  Hunt recondites from 20-24.<br><br>Now that I am 24 I am gonna head to Marus Seru.  Hope this guide is useful.<br><br>Darkdirk Devertebrater 55 blackguard<br>Inumbro 24 battleshaman<br>&nbsp;<br>Darkdirk Devertebrater, 55 rogue<br>Penumbro Deathblow, 20 SK<br>Teque No, 21 bard<br><br>Proud to be one of 10 people who isn't an idiot in EQ<br><br>Povar server<br></td></tr>
