	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just got my lvl 45 lastnight real late and did not have time to truely test my JBB. Was wondering if there were any shaman out there who could give me some tips on the best method of using the JBB.<br><br>I was thinking this:<br><br>1) Set up camp with pet.<br><br>2) Buff both me and pet.<br><br>3) Pull with slow to camp.<br><br>4) Root mob disempower.<br><br>5) Then start casting JBB and maybe a dot.(want to save as much mana as possible)<br><br>6) Only send in pet if mob hits me???(cast on JBB is 8 ticks)<br><br>Is saving mana by relying on JBB too time consuming and ultimately a waste of time? Should I refrain from relying so much on this mana free dd?<br><br>I am also wondering if it would help to get a focus item from a Mage to increase cast time on JBB?? Any thoughts anyone?<br>&nbsp;<br>Money<br>46 Shammy Barbarian<br>Full Juandiced 1044 AC<br><br>Who knew it would happen to you???</td></tr>
