<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10332918659800></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10332918659800><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=10332918659800>RE: JBB</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=10332918659800#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=147821><span id=Sage>Aggrok</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>102 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Sep 29th 5:47 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.70]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;   Your strategy is pretty good, although I rarely malosi mobs because anything that you are fighting high enuff to need a debuff usually resists the debuff too. I would definately pull with a slow spell no matter what mob you are fighting, I use walking sleep for easy ( green / light blue mobs ) as its only 60 mana for 30% slow, which is enuff time to get the mob dead before your pets bites it. Use Togors / Turgurs for blue+ mobs. Always pull because then you can control exactly where the mob engages your pet. Leave pet taunting on, you want the mob to stay on him because he has much better regen ( especially with your chloro/regrowth, which the pet should ALWAYS have on ). No need to root the mob, even when you pull with a slow spell. Just send your pet after the mob when it arives at the spot you want your pet to engage it with taunting on and the mob will go after the pet most if the time, if not within a few seconds of the pet hitting on it while you kite it ( I know, druid-like but effective for the few embarassing seconds its necessary ). When you get Harnessing of Spirit ( HoS ) at 49 use it w/ JB STR and DEX buffs since they now stack again, your pet can use those extra 250 hp. If he doesn't need them you are pulling too slow or fighting mobs too low a level. I buff pet with everything usually because pets die too quick fighting XP giving mobs even slowed or with JBB--if you want to fight with an unbuffed pet make a cleric--their pets are called tanks ( hehe j/k :) ). But if you dont want to give pet all you have atleast keep up JB buffs, haste, and regen. By level 45 I had moved to DL and BW, and by 51 BW and Skyfire ( all nice and close to one another for us non porting classes ). Soloing gets MUCH easier at 54-56 when you get Can 3, 55 pet and celerity ( and Bane of Nife if you are lucky ). These 3 levels represent a huge power increase for shaman, enjoy them cause you will suck until you are level 60 with all your spells ( we have no offensive capability increases from 57-59 excpet Pox of Bertoxxulous, a very rare spell that sells for 30k on Luclin *IF* its for sale ). NEVER sell your JBB, they are going up in price everyday on Luclin, been offered 19k for it twice last week and refused. Only a Fungi Tunic will help you solo nearly as well as a JBB, and only then really at 54 cause of Can3. <br>     Basically after a fight I want my pet at around 30% life and me at 60% mana/health. This usually gets us to full health/mana at about the same time, which makes the most of your pulls as you dont want to be sitting with full mana while your pet is healing or you OOM and pet full health. The mobs you choose are up to you--basically you have 2 types--runners and non-runners. Non runners like hornets are nice cause they never aggro more mobs running before you are ready for them, but do more damage to your pet before they die. Runners like giants will save a little beating on your pet but pathing can be a problem with other mobs aggroing you or pet. Never let a pet drop below 25% life as mobs tend to frenzy on low life pets or PC's instead of run, and spending 1000-2000 mana to make and rebuff a pet that a 200 mana heal could have saved is stupid. If you find your pet needs heals from a full health pull, you are pulling mobs too high for level, not using a good enuff slow spell, or not dotting any ( I use E bolt on the harder blues ). Considering our DoTs suck till 49 you may be better chain pulling light blues for XP rather than long fights with harder mobs using alot more mana.<br>   BTW, even at 8 second cast time 263DD for 0 mana expenditure is much better than medding for that 8 sec. The JBB has a very good range for a click item, you can get pretty far away from the mob and nuke the mess out of it and usually have time to root it if it makes a break for you ( maybe you get hit once, no big deal if unstunnable ogre :) ).<br>   Mage items DECREASE cast time, if they have any effect at all, not sure on that one.<br>   Also, 1044 AC is about 200 more AC than I normally run w/o buffs, and while its great you may want to change out some AC for HP/Mana gear or resists while fighting AE mobs. AC means nothing if you arent getting hit, and while fighting with a JBB and pet that shouldn't happen very often. Since you are vulnerable to stuns as a barbarian, I would avoid melee, unless you have a kick-butt 2hb, a haste item and alacrity on you at all times. It just wont be worth getting hit and losing all those hp which equal mana and possibly getting stunned and losing out even more. Even I as an ogre shaman have all but given up melee with the JBB.\<br>    I did read the other posts about this and I wanted to mention a few ( more !! ) things:<br>     Using Flash of Light / Blinding Luminescence is a great theory, but in practical use really blows. Yes, they are low mana and quick-casting, but are resisted too much, too unpredictable in nature as for duration, and since we lack a snare spell ( except Innoruuk trolls who do the Neriak quests ), chasing a fleeing mob at full speed is a pain in the a$$. You will definately need to keep your pet SoWed if you do this ( a spell I dont normally have memmed as I have epic boots ). Depending on where you choose to fight pathing of mobs may prevent you from using blind kiting due to adds or warping/&quot;gating&quot; mobs. Even blinded mobs will turn to hit you ( and your pet too if I recall ) if either of you are in melee range, unlike a fear spell. If you insist on using a ghetto fear spell expect ghetto XP increases (no disrespect Ungel, but even if you like blind kiting it absolutely cannot be done in a dungeon environment).<br>    My spell lineup at level 55 consists of this: 1. Superior heal ( raely used, for hard mobs/emergencies). 2. Regrowth ( chloro at your level ). 3. Cannibalize 3 4. Alacrity ( or celerity once i hit 56 ) 5. Walking Sleep ( 30% slow @ level 55 ). 6. Root. 7. E bolt ( or best poison DoT your have ) 8. Turgur's Insects ( 70% slow at level 55, not 75% until level 60 ). When/if I need to buff pet I usually switch out slot 4 and 5 , and I have all my normal spell line-up on page 1 of my spell book to save time. I still use the OLD UI as I dont feel like memming 100 new icons for spells effects and that see thru/transparent windows irritate me. :)<br>  Long post, hope it helps out any you and any future shaman. <br>     Edit: Forgot 2 things. The whole disepower/listless power/incapacitate/cripple line has very little effect on NPC's . I only use them on &quot;epic&quot; tyoe fights where even a few % decrease of the mobs abilities may make or break the fight. Now in PvP/Duels its godly, as dropping a melee classes STR and AGI can get the basically so encumbered the are better than snared.<br>      Also, to completely answer the post I responded to, from what I have been told by several shaman, click items ( like JBB ) are not affected by focus items, ie you cant make the spell cast quicker, do more damage or increase the effetive range. I have a few level 2 affliction items now and Ill try them out to see what the real deal is, but I believe the many people who told me these do not work on click items. Would be nice but not possible as far as I know at this point ( if they all did, you would have a nearly 300hp mana free DD that cast in lik e 6 to 6.5 seconds instead of 8 with a near 300 ft range--sweet but I could see that getting nerfed real quick )<br>    Please post ideas you have for our class. Even tho I have a way I usually do things, that can change at any time ( and I have changed strategies lots over the levels ) and alot of that credit goes to fellow shaman that post on this board.  Keep up the good work.<br><br>55 Ogre Luminary on Luclin server--Choatic Winds--Baron Aggrok<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Oct 16 08:20:56 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
