	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's how i would use it (solo of course)...<br><br>Pull the mob with the jbb, ask pet to attack (with taunt off!). When the mob gets too close, cast Blind on it, then jbb it again. Your pet will do some damage while surviving the fight, and if you cast your Blind spell at the proper time, you should get out of the fight without getting hit.<br>This leaves you with a lot of mana to buff you and your pet (alacrity, sow, str, dex, etc...). Alternatively, you may wish to pull with a dot. The key is to keep the agro on you, and keep that mob blinded as much as possible.<br>It might not be the best way to use the jbb, but its a lot of fun :)<br><br>Oh, and it works great even if you dont have a jbb :)<br><br>Ungel<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
